## Step 7: GitLab and CI/CD

GitLab and the GitLab Runner are NixOS VMs on the **management network**
(native/untagged VLAN). GitLab has a Let's Encrypt certificate via certbot
with explicit FQDN support. The runner is stateless and fully rebuildable.

> **Deployment model:** GitLab and the runner are **Tier 2** (workstation-managed).
> The pipeline cannot deploy the infrastructure it runs on. See architecture.md
> section 10.3 for the two-tier deployment model.

### 7.1 Prerequisites

Before deploying GitLab:
- [ ] DNS record `gitlab.{{ environments.prod.dns_domain }}` exists pointing to `{{ vms.gitlab.ip }}`
- [ ] Prod DNS servers are reachable from management network (for certbot DNS-01)
- [ ] DHCP reservation for GitLab: MAC `{{ vms.gitlab.mac }}` → `{{ vms.gitlab.ip }}`
- [ ] DHCP reservation for Runner: MAC `{{ vms.cicd.mac }}` → `{{ vms.cicd.ip }}`

Verify DNS:
```bash
dig gitlab.{{ environments.prod.dns_domain }} @{{ vms.dns1_prod.ip }}
# Expected: {{ vms.gitlab.ip }}
```

### 7.2 Build and Deploy GitLab

```bash
# Build the GitLab image (this takes a while — GitLab CE is large)
framework/scripts/build-image.sh site/nix/hosts/gitlab.nix gitlab

# Deploy
cd site/tofu
framework/scripts/tofu-wrapper.sh apply -target=module.gitlab
```

GitLab takes 5–10 minutes to start on first boot (database migrations, asset
compilation). Wait for it to become accessible:

```bash
# Wait for GitLab API
while ! curl -sk https://{{ vms.gitlab.ip }}/api/v4/version 2>/dev/null | jq -r '.version'; do
  echo "Waiting for GitLab..."; sleep 15
done
```

- [ ] GitLab VM deployed
- [ ] GitLab API accessible at `https://gitlab.{{ environments.prod.dns_domain }}`
- [ ] TLS certificate is from Let's Encrypt (not self-signed)

### 7.3 Configure GitLab

```bash
framework/scripts/configure-gitlab.sh
```

This script:
1. Waits for GitLab to be accessible
2. Retrieves the initial root password and stores it in SOPS
3. Creates the `infra` project
4. Generates a runner registration token and stores it in SOPS

After running:
- [ ] Log into GitLab web UI and change the root password
- [ ] Update SOPS with new password:
  ```bash
  sops --set '["gitlab_root_password"] "<new-password>"' site/sops/secrets.yaml
  ```
- [ ] Push the repository:
  ```bash
  git remote add gitlab https://gitlab.{{ environments.prod.dns_domain }}/root/infra.git
  git push gitlab --all
  ```

### 7.4 Build and Deploy the Runner

```bash
# Build the Runner image
framework/scripts/build-image.sh site/nix/hosts/cicd.nix cicd

# Deploy
framework/scripts/tofu-wrapper.sh apply -target=module.cicd

# HA double-apply (if VMID changes)
framework/scripts/tofu-wrapper.sh apply -target=module.cicd
```

- [ ] Runner VM deployed at `{{ vms.cicd.ip }}`

### 7.5 Register the Runner

```bash
framework/scripts/register-runner.sh
```

Verify:
```bash
# Runner has all required tools
ssh root@{{ vms.cicd.ip }} "which bash nix tofu sops yq jq curl git dig openssl"

# Runner is online in GitLab
# Check GitLab web UI → Admin → Runners
```

- [ ] Runner registered and online in GitLab
- [ ] Runner has infra and deploy tags

### 7.6 Test the Pipeline

1. Push a change to the `dev` branch on GitLab
2. Verify pipeline runs: validate → build → deploy-dev → test-dev
3. Verify content-addressed naming: unchanged roles produce same filenames
4. Verify no unnecessary VM recreation

- [ ] Pipeline runs on push to dev
- [ ] Dev deployment works via CI/CD
- [ ] No VMs recreated for unchanged roles (content-addressed naming)

### 7.7 Control-Plane Update Procedure

GitLab and the runner are Tier 2 — update from the workstation only:

```bash
# Update order: GitLab first, then runner (runner registration is in GitLab's DB)

# 1. Update GitLab
framework/scripts/build-image.sh site/nix/hosts/gitlab.nix gitlab
framework/scripts/tofu-wrapper.sh apply -target=module.gitlab
# Wait for GitLab to become accessible (~5 min on first boot)

# 2. Update Runner
framework/scripts/build-image.sh site/nix/hosts/cicd.nix cicd
framework/scripts/tofu-wrapper.sh apply -target=module.cicd
framework/scripts/register-runner.sh
```

### 7.8 Backup and Recovery

GitLab is included in the PBS backup job alongside Vault VMs:

```bash
# Verify backup job includes GitLab
ssh root@{{ nodes[0].mgmt_ip }} "pvesh get /cluster/backup --output-format json" | jq '.[].vmid'

# Manual backup test
GITLAB_VMID=$(ssh root@{{ nodes[0].mgmt_ip }} "qm list" | grep gitlab | awk '{print $1}')
ssh root@{{ nodes[0].mgmt_ip }} "vzdump $GITLAB_VMID --storage pbs-nas --mode snapshot --compress zstd"

# Configure ZFS replication for both VMs
framework/scripts/configure-replication.sh gitlab
framework/scripts/configure-replication.sh cicd
```

- [ ] GitLab backup job created and tested
- [ ] ZFS replication configured for GitLab and Runner

